        <p class="title"><%= title %></p>
        <br>
        <p id="description"> In academia and industry, writing letters of recommendation is a very
            important, but sometimes repetitive task. Many faculty and professionals already have a standard template
            that they merely customize for each request. Others may ask the requester to
            write the recommendation themselves, then all they need to do is verify that the letter is accurate before signing.
            Although this sometimes works, the process would be much smoother and accurate if the student requesting
            the recommendation could provide information to the writer ahead of time.
        <br><br>
            This application allows the individual requesting a recommendation to submit all
            of the information they want included through a form, and the 
            writer can automatically pull that information
            into a template that they have created. After the letter has been generated,
            the recommender can download it ensure its accuracy. After the
            recommender approves it, the original requester can also download the
            electronic version of the letter.
        </p>
